&lt;p data-start=&quot;599&quot; data-end=&quot;622&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Position Overview&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p data-start=&quot;623&quot; data-end=&quot;1293&quot;&gt;The Lab Assistant plays an important role in supporting laboratory operations and patient care within West Cancer Center. This position is responsible for preparing stains, solutions, and culture media, performing waived and moderately complex laboratory tests, and maintaining accurate specimen records. The Lab Assistant also assists with venipuncture as requested by the directing physician and helps ensure a safe and efficient laboratory environment by following all safety and infection control protocols. This role requires strong attention to detail, adaptability in a clinical setting, and a commitment to upholding West Cancer Center’s vision and values.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p data-start=&quot;1295&quot; data-end=&quot;1321&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
