&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Title: &lt;/strong&gt;Licensed Master Social Worker&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Us&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;At West Cancer Center, we are dedicated to providing compassionate, patient-centered care while advancing groundbreaking research. Our team fosters collaboration, innovation, and professional growth, ensuring that every role contributes to making a difference in patients’ lives. Join us in our mission to provide comprehensive support to those navigating the challenges of cancer treatment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Position Overview&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;The Licensed Master Social Worker provides assistance to patients and families in identifying social, emotional, environmental, and financial needs. This role addresses these needs directly or through referrals, connecting patients with available resources and services within the clinic or community. The Licensed Master Social Worker conducts psychosocial assessments, provides counseling and interventions, and collaborates with the care team to address the psychosocial needs of patients and their families.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Gather and assess information regarding patients’ physical needs, mental status, family support, financial resources, and potential barriers to care.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct psychosocial assessments of patients and families and develop plans to address identified needs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop personalized care plans in coordination with the patient, care providers, and patient support team.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide direct interventions including individual, family, or group counseling and crisis intervention as needed.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide psycho-social support to patients and their families or caregivers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Act as an advocate for patients and families.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Remain current on community and governmental resources and refer patients to appropriate programs as needed.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain appropriate documentation and statistical data.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Communicate with physicians and nurses regarding psychosocial health issues and patient/family needs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Interface with community organizations and programs to support patient resources.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain patient dignity, confidentiality, professionalism, and compliance with clinic policies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Attend staff meetings as scheduled and participate in a team-oriented environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform other duties as assigned.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Education &amp;amp; Experience&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Required:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Master’s degree from an accredited School of Social Work.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;One (1) year of professional practice post-graduation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Preferred:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in Oncology or a healthcare setting.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Credential/Licensure&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Required:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Licensed Master Social Worker (LMSW).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Skills &amp;amp; Abilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Knowledge of oncology disease processes and their effects on patients and families.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Knowledge of insurance, state and federal regulations, and resources specific to oncology.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Knowledge of social work theory, crisis intervention, and individual, group, and family therapy.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent organizational and follow-up skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong verbal and written communication skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong problem-solving abilities.&lt;/li&g

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Title: &lt;/strong&gt;Mammography Tech&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Us&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;West Cancer Center is a comprehensive, patient-centered cancer care and research institution committed to compassionate care, innovation, and clinical excellence. Our multidisciplinary teams deliver integrated care tailored to the needs of each individual and their loved ones.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Position Overview&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Mammography Tech is responsible for operating imaging equipment to perform procedures for a specified patient population. This role requires precision, professionalism, and a commitment to delivering quality patient care in accordance with West Cancer Center’s Mission, Vision, and Values.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform quality radiologic procedures using appropriate technical and safety methods&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor and ensure compliance with regulatory requirements, quality standards, policies, and procedures&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage resources effectively, including supplies and equipment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrate professionalism and excellent customer service in all interactions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain compliance with safety protocols and infection control measures&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide occasional demonstration and instruction to student technologists&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform other job-related functions as assigned&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Education &amp;amp; Experience&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Required:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Completion of a formal education program in radiography accredited by a mechanism acceptable to ARRT&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Certification and registration as R.T. (R) ARRT&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Must obtain certification and registry in Mammography within six months of hire&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;State license in accordance with state regulations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;BLS Certification through the American Heart Association&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Skills &amp;amp; Abilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Basic knowledge of radiographic equipment and imaging procedures&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Effective communication and interpersonal skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Basic knowledge of radiology information systems (RIS, HIS, and PACS preferred)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Why West Cancer Center is a Great Place to Work&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Meaningful Impact&lt;/strong&gt;: Play a direct role in supporting patients through one of the most challenging times of their lives.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Collaborative Culture&lt;/strong&gt;: Work alongside a multidisciplinary team of dedicated professionals committed to improving cancer care.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Professional Development&lt;/strong&gt;: Benefit from ongoing training, educational resources, and growth opportunities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Mission-Driven Environment&lt;/strong&gt;: Be part of an organization guided by compassion, integrity, and innovation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;No nights, weekends, or holidays.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
