&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Title: &lt;/strong&gt;Medical Laboratory Technician&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Us&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;West Cancer Center is a leading, mission-driven organization dedicated to providing exceptional cancer care with compassion and innovation. Our multidisciplinary teams are united by a shared vision to improve outcomes and quality of life for every patient we serve. We invite you to join our community and help transform cancer care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Position Overview&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Medical Laboratory Technician plays a critical role in supporting the diagnosis and treatment of cancer patients by performing technical laboratory testing on patient specimens. Working under the direction of a licensed Medical Technologist, this role ensures accuracy, efficiency, and compliance with professional laboratory standards.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform accurate and appropriate laboratory testing of patient specimens under supervision&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Report test results promptly and according to established laboratory procedures&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Adhere to quality control procedures, compliance regulations, and standard operating policies&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist in managing lab resources, instruments, and workflow for efficient operations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain safety standards while working with hazardous materials and patient specimens&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform additional duties as assigned&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Education &amp;amp; Experience&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Required:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Associate’s degree in Medical Laboratory Technology (including those grandfathered in from CLA programs)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Current licensure as a Medical Laboratory Technician in the state of Tennessee (required only for TN-based positions)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Substitutions Allowed:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Graduation from a military medical laboratory program&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Skills &amp;amp; Abilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Working knowledge of clinical laboratory procedures and instrumentation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Effective verbal and written communication skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with laboratory information systems&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to manage tasks independently and prioritize effectively&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Team-oriented mindset and ability to communicate across clinical departments&lt;/li&gt;
