&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Title: &lt;/strong&gt;Oncology Nurse Navigator&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Us&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;West Cancer Center is a comprehensive oncology practice where compassionate care meets innovative medicine. Our mission is to support every patient on their journey with expert care, empathy, and cutting-edge treatments. Our team of specialists works together to guide each patient through every step of the cancer experience—from diagnosis through survivorship.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Position Overview&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Oncology Nurse Navigator serves as a dedicated care coordinator throughout the cancer care continuum. This role assesses and addresses the physical, emotional, and social needs of patients, while working closely with healthcare providers and internal/external partners to remove barriers to care. ONNs provide education, improve access, and streamline communication to ensure a supportive, seamless experience for patients and their families.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
