&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Title: &lt;/strong&gt;Radiology Tech&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Us&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;At West Cancer Center, we are dedicated to providing compassionate, patient-centered care while advancing groundbreaking research. Our team fosters collaboration, innovation, and professional growth, ensuring that every role contributes to making a difference in patients’ lives. Join us in our mission to provide comprehensive support to those navigating the challenges of cancer treatment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Position Overview&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;The Rad Tech is responsible for operating imaging equipment to perform radiologic procedures for a specified patient population. This role ensures quality imaging services while adhering to regulatory standards and organizational policies. The Rad Tech&amp;nbsp; models behavior consistent with West Cancer Center’s Mission, Vision, and Values.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform quality radiologic procedures using appropriate technical and safety methods.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure compliance with regulatory requirements, quality standards, and organizational policies and procedures.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage resources such as supplies and equipment effectively.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Plan and complete job responsibilities in an efficient and productive manner.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrate professional behavior and provide excellent customer service in all interactions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Observe and instruct student technologists and occasionally demonstrate job responsibilities to other associates as needed.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Education &amp;amp; Experience&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Completion of a formal education program in radiography accredited by a mechanism acceptable to ARRT.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Credential/Licensure&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Certification and registration as R.T. (R) ARRT.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;State license in accordance with regulations in the state where work is performed.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Basic Life Support (BLS) certification through the American Heart Association (required for all new hires and transfers).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Substitution&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;New graduates of an accredited radiography program without ARRT primary certification must obtain certification and registry as R.T. (R) (ARRT) within one year of graduation from an approved program.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Skills &amp;amp; Abilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Basic knowledge of radiographic equipment and imaging procedures.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to effectively relate and communicate with internal and external customers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Basic knowledge of radiology information systems (RIS, HIS, and PACS preferred as stated in source).&lt;/li&gt;
